{
  "texts": [
    "One famous sonnet by William Shakespeare is \"Sonnet 18,\" which includes the quote: \"Shall I compare thee to a summer's day?\" 3.",
    "Immanuel Kant's three critiques are:",
    "Critique of Pure Reason (1781): This critique established the foundation of Kant's philosophy, including his theories on knowledge, reality, and ethics.",
    "It introduced the concept of the \"transcendental aesthetic\" and the \"categorical imperative.\" 2.",
    "Critique of Practical Reason (1788): This critique focused on morality and ethics, introducing the concept of the \"categorical imperative\" as a moral principle."
  ]
}